## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- Node.js v18 or higher
- PostgreSQL 14 or higher
- npm

### 1. Clone the repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/marketnest.git
cd marketnest
```

### 2. Set up the database

Open PostgreSQL and create the database:

```sql
CREATE DATABASE marketnest;
```

Then run your schema file to create all tables:

```bash
psql -U postgres -d marketnest -f schema.sql
```

### 3. Configure the backend

Go into the backend folder and create a `.env` file:

```bash
cd backend
```

Create `.env` with these values:

```
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:YOUR_PASSWORD@localhost:5432/marketnest
JWT_SECRET=your_secret_key_here
PORT=5000
FRONTEND_URL=http://localhost:5173
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=your_anthropic_key_here
```

Install dependencies and start the backend:

```bash
npm install
npm run dev
```

The backend will run on `http://localhost:5000`.

### 4. Configure the frontend

Open a new terminal and go into the frontend folder:

```bash
cd frontend
```

Create a `.env` file:

```
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:5000
```

Install dependencies and start the frontend:

```bash
npm install
npm run dev
```

The frontend will run on `http://localhost:5173`.

